<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="165" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="165">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="165">
Total body length ranged between 10.8 and 11.5 mm and tail 27.3-33.7% of body length. Hooks 8-10. Anterior teeth 14. Slender and transparent body (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="F11" captionText="Figure 11. A Krohnitta subtilis (dorsal view) B head C tail D lateral fin. Abbreviations: CC = corona ciliata; CF = caudal fin; COL = collarette; E = eye; GS = grasping spine; IN = intestine; LF = lateral fin; RLZ = Ray less zone; SV = seminal vesicle." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704195" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">11A</figureCitation>
). Small head. One row of stout teeth arranged in fan shape (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Number and shape of dentition A Ferosagitta robusta (two rows) B Krohnitta subtilis (one row)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704193" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">9B</figureCitation>
). Collarette and intestinal diverticula absent (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="F11" captionText="Figure 11. A Krohnitta subtilis (dorsal view) B head C tail D lateral fin. Abbreviations: CC = corona ciliata; CF = caudal fin; COL = collarette; E = eye; GS = grasping spine; IN = intestine; LF = lateral fin; RLZ = Ray less zone; SV = seminal vesicle." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704195" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">11B</figureCitation>
). Grasping spine abruptly curved (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Grasping spine A abruptly curved hooks (Krohnitta subtilis, Krohnittidae) B gently curved and not serrated hooks (Ferosagitta robusta, Sagittidae) C gently curved and serrated hooks (Serratosagitta pacifica, Sagittidae)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704192" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">8A</figureCitation>
). Round eyes with eye pigments in 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“E”">&quot;E&quot;</normalizedToken>
shape (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="F11" captionText="Figure 11. A Krohnitta subtilis (dorsal view) B head C tail D lateral fin. Abbreviations: CC = corona ciliata; CF = caudal fin; COL = collarette; E = eye; GS = grasping spine; IN = intestine; LF = lateral fin; RLZ = Ray less zone; SV = seminal vesicle." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704195" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">11B</figureCitation>
). Corona ciliata beginning in front of eyes with round shape (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="F11" captionText="Figure 11. A Krohnitta subtilis (dorsal view) B head C tail D lateral fin. Abbreviations: CC = corona ciliata; CF = caudal fin; COL = collarette; E = eye; GS = grasping spine; IN = intestine; LF = lateral fin; RLZ = Ray less zone; SV = seminal vesicle." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704195" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">11C</figureCitation>
). Lateral fins 29.4% of body length. Starting points of lateral fins 54.3% and ending points of lateral fins 82.2% of body length, respectively. One pair of lateral fins only rayed on outer edge, with forward ends equidistant from caudal septum (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="F11" captionText="Figure 11. A Krohnitta subtilis (dorsal view) B head C tail D lateral fin. Abbreviations: CC = corona ciliata; CF = caudal fin; COL = collarette; E = eye; GS = grasping spine; IN = intestine; LF = lateral fin; RLZ = Ray less zone; SV = seminal vesicle." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704195" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">11A, E</figureCitation>
). Caudal fin roughly round in shape (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="F11" captionText="Figure 11. A Krohnitta subtilis (dorsal view) B head C tail D lateral fin. Abbreviations: CC = corona ciliata; CF = caudal fin; COL = collarette; E = eye; GS = grasping spine; IN = intestine; LF = lateral fin; RLZ = Ray less zone; SV = seminal vesicle." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704195" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">11D</figureCitation>
). Seminal vesicles elongated with anterolateral-edge-opening touching both lateral fins and caudal fin (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="F11" captionText="Figure 11. A Krohnitta subtilis (dorsal view) B head C tail D lateral fin. Abbreviations: CC = corona ciliata; CF = caudal fin; COL = collarette; E = eye; GS = grasping spine; IN = intestine; LF = lateral fin; RLZ = Ray less zone; SV = seminal vesicle." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704195" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">11D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
